async function makePlanksAndPlaceChest(bot, chestCount = 1, preferredPlank = "birch_planks", placeRadius = 6, keepPlanks = 0) {
    // It validates inputs and calculates how many planks are required for the requested number of chests, then checks current plank inventory and whether a crafting table block is already placed nearby; it then invokes a child routine to craft and place the crafting table and chests and waits for inventory synchronization. After the child routine completes it recomputes plank totals and, if the inventory has fewer planks than the requested keepPlanks, crafts additional plank recipe executions using the preferred plank variant or falling back to any available planks until the target is met (or throws on failure). Finally it scans for chest blocks within the specified placement radius and returns the final plank count and the positions of any found chests, throwing errors on invalid inputs, craft failures, or if no chest is located nearby.
}

