async function depositUselessItemsSafe(bot, chestPosition = null, minCount = 16, extraBlacklist = [], maxChestTries = 5) {
    // The function gathers inventory totals and builds a deposit list by excluding a default keep set plus any provided extra blacklist, only including item types whose total count meets or exceeds minCount. It validates the bot and that chests are available, then resolves chest candidates using an optional user-specified position first and by searching nearby chests within 32 blocks (limited to maxChestTries). It attempts to deposit the selected items into each candidate in sequence, recording failures and continuing to the next, and if all nearby attempts fail it optionally teleports to the first candidate and retries once. On success it returns the deposited item summary and the chest position used; if all attempts fail it throws an error summarizing the failures.
}

