async function ensureCoalOrCharcoal(bot, targetCount = 8, exploreTime = 60) {
    // Ensures the bot has a specified number of coal/charcoal (default 8) by checking inventory and, if short, searching nearby and briefly exploring to find and mine coal ore while equipping the best available pickaxe; if mining yields enough it returns the updated total. If mining doesn't suffice, it falls back to producing charcoal by gathering or mining logs (exploring for trees if necessary), ensuring a furnace is placed or crafted nearby, choosing an available fuel, and smelting the required number of logs into charcoal. The procedure updates counts after each step and returns the final total when the target is reached or throws an error if resources, fuel, or placement fail.
}

