async function craftGoldenApple(bot, count = 1, maxTableDistance = 32, placeRadius = 6, exploreTime = 60) {
    // This routine prepares and crafts a given number of golden apples for the bot: it first validates inputs and that the server recognizes apples and gold ingots, then computes required materials (8 gold ingots and 1 apple per golden apple) and checks inventory; if apples are missing it attempts a single nearby leaf-break to obtain one, and if gold ingots are short it triggers smelting/mining routines to reach the target total; it then ensures a crafting table is available within the specified distance (placing one if necessary) and performs the crafting of the requested golden apples; any failure in obtaining materials, ensuring the table, or crafting results in a thrown error, and on success it returns the final count of golden apples in inventory.
}

