async function ensureLapis(bot, targetTotal = 8, exploreTime = 60, maxAttempts = 3) {
    // Validates the bot and target, then ensures the bot has at least the desired number of lapis_lazuli (default 8) by checking inventory and repeatedly searching for nearby lapis ore within ~32 blocks (or exploring downward for a set time) up to a maximum number of attempts; when ore is found it moves nearby, computes how many ore blocks to mine using a conservative yield estimate (4 lapis per ore), mines that many blocks, waits for inventory sync, and updates the count; the process repeats until the target is reached or attempts are exhausted, returning the current lapis count on success and throwing an error on failure.
}

